# API Route Rules

## Handler shape

1. Parse and validate input (Zod)
2. Verify Firebase ID token from `Authorization` header
3. Map `firebase_uid` → internal `users.id`
4. Call service/repository
5. Return typed JSON or standard error envelope

## Error envelope

```json
{ "code": "forbidden", "message": "...", "details": {}, "requestId": "..." }
```

## AuthZ

- Never accept `userId` from client body/query
- Group writes: check `group_members.role` (`owner`/`admin` for invites and group favorites)
- Members can read group resources they belong to

## Idempotency

- `PUT /api/favorites/:placeId` for upsert
- `DELETE` for removals
- Wrap multi-write ops (create group + owner membership) in transactions

## External APIs

- Proxy Overpass/Nominatim through server (CORS + normalization)
- Set timeouts; cache by lat/lng/radius bucket when reasonable

## Naming

- DTOs end with `Dto`; DB row types end with `Row`
